Step 1: Check and Set Java Path
Run this command in your Linux terminal:
find / -type f -name java

🔹 Step 2: Install Maven
sudo apt update
sudo apt install maven -y
java -version
mvn -version

🔹 Step 3: Configure Jenkins Tools

Open Jenkins → Manage Jenkins → Global Tool Configuration
Scroll to JDK section:
Uncheck “Install automatically”
Name: Java17
JAVA_HOME: /usr/lib/jvm/java-17-openjdk-amd64

Scroll to Maven section:
Check “Install automatically”
Name: Maven

Scroll to Git section:
Check “Install automatically”
Click Save

